nd out more about the `-H:TempDirectory=` option for GraalVM Native Image. I think this option specifies a temporary directory, and it seems I could set it with `-H:TempDirectory=<path>`. There's also a question of whether I could use `--temp-dir`. I’m curious if it’s possible to check the native image with expert options or if maybe I should grep the binary or use strings with `rg` in the GRAALVM_HOME.\\\"}]}\"}, {\"type\": \"toolCall\", \"id\": \"call_jNioLzpfZbx8zGYmcWMXe8VX|fc_0df91dfc7677ce0d0169fe34da049481939aa84e188b985cc9\", \"name\": \"bash\", \"arguments\": {\"command\": \"rg \\\"TempDirectory|temp directory|driverRoot\\\" /home/vjovanov/c/g/vj/forge/ce/sdk/mxbuild/linux-amd64/GRAALVM_JAVA25/graalvm-25.1.0-dev+10.1/lib/svm -n --hidden --glob '!**/*.o' --glob '!**/*.a' | head -50\", \"timeout\": 20}}], \"api\": \"openai-responses\", \"provider\": \"OCA\", \"model\": \"gpt-5.5\", \"usage\": {\"input\": 24045, \"output\": 739, \"cacheRead\": 60928, \"cacheWrite\": 0, \"totalTokens\": 85712, \"cost\": {\"input\": 0, \"output\": 0, \"cacheRead\": 0, \"cacheWrite\": 0, \"total\": 0}}, \"stopReason\": \"toolUse\", \"timestamp\": 1778267327828, \"responseId\": \"resp_0df91dfc7677ce0d0169fe34c28fc48193b956b5b02ccdb637\"}}\n[tool-exec] start id=call_jNioLzpfZbx8zGYmcWMXe8VX|fc_0df91dfc7677ce0d0169fe34da049481939aa84e188b985cc9 name=bash args={\"command\": \"rg \\\"TempDirectory|temp directory|driverRoot\\\" /home/vjovanov/c/g/vj/forge/ce/sdk/mxbuild/linux-amd64/GRAALVM_JAVA25/graalvm-25.1.0-dev+10.1/lib/svm -n --hidden --glob '!**/*.o' --glob '!**/*.a' | head -50\", \"timeout\": 20}\n[tool-exec] update id=call_jNioLzpfZbx8zGYmcWMXe8VX|fc_0df91dfc7677ce0d0169fe34da049481939aa84e188b985cc9 name=bash\n[tool-exec] update id=call_jNioLzpfZbx8zGYmcWMXe8VX|fc_0df91dfc7677ce0d0169fe34da049481939aa84e188b985cc9 name=bash\n  x.RegularExpression$Context\"},{\"id\":204,\"name\":\"com.sun.org.apache.xerces.internal.impl.xpath.regex.RegularExpression$ExpressionTarget\"},{\"id\":