igating build.gradle issues**\\\\n\\\\nI’m looking into why build.gradle creates files in /dev/shm, which might be mounted noexec. It seems like tmpfs could be causing some issues due to inodes or permissions. Maybe the specific subdirectory isn’t writable because it was created by a previous user, even though it's the same user.\\\\n\\\\nI wonder if native-image is creating a large \\\\\\\"driverRoot-\\\\\\\" in the current directory. Additionally, ArchiveSupport.createTempDir likely uses Files.createTempDirectory(Path.of(\\\\\\\".\\\\\\\")), but it might not respect java.io.tmpdir. I’ll need to explore system properties and how they interact, especially with native executables I suppose.\\\"},{\\\"type\\\":\\\"summary_text\\\",\\\"text\\\":\\\"**Exploring native-image settings**\\\\n\\\\nI’m considering how \\\\\\\"native-image\\\\\\\" works as a native executable built with substrate. It seems like -J-D options might be ignored for its own system properties, and perhaps these are passed to the builder instead. The early driver doesn’t seem to see them.\\\\n\\\\nI'm thinking the environment variable TMPDIR might not be applied by the plugin. Should I use `buildArgs.add(\\\\\\\"-Djava.io.tmpdir=...\\\\\\\")` to set the property in the image being built? However, using `JAVA_TOOL_OPTIONS` with that might not work for the native binary.\\\"},{\\\"type\\\":\\\"summary_text\\\",\\\"text\\\":\\\"**Exploring GraalVM options**\\\\n\\\\nI need to find out more about the `-H:TempDirectory=` option for GraalVM Native Image. I think this option specifies a temporary directory, and it seems I could set it with `-H:TempDirectory=<path>`. There's also a question of whether I could use `--temp-dir`. I’m curious if it’s possible to check the native image with expert options or if maybe I should grep the binary or use strings with `rg` in the GRAALVM_HOME.\\\"}]}\"}, {\"type\": \"toolCall\", \"id\": \"call_jNioLzpfZbx8zGYmcWMXe8VX|fc_0df91dfc7677ce0d0169fe34da049481939aa84e188b985cc9\", \"name\": \"bash\", \"arguments\": {\"command\": \"rg \\\"TempDirectory|temp directory|driverRoot\\\" /home/vjovanov/c/g/vj/forge/ce/sdk/mxbuild/linux-amd64/GRAALVM_JAVA25/graalvm-25.1.0-dev+10.1/lib/svm -n --hidden --glob '!**/*.o' --glob '!**/*.a' | head -50\", \"timeout\": 20}}], \"api\": \"openai-responses\", \"provider\": \"OCA\", \"model\": \"gpt-5.5\", \"usage\": {\"input\": 24045, \"output\": 739, \"cacheRead\": 60928, \"cacheWrite\": 0, \"totalTokens\": 85712, \"cost\": {\"input\": 0, \"output\": 0, \"cacheRead\": 0, \"cacheWrite\": 0, \"total\": 0}}, \"stopReason\": \"toolUse\", \"timestamp\": 1778267327828, \"responseId\": \"resp_0df91dfc7677ce0d0169fe34c28fc48193b956b5b02ccdb637\"}}\n13550:  x.RegularExpression$Context\"},{\"id\":204,\"name\":\"com.sun.org.apache.xerces.internal.impl.xpath.regex.RegularExpression$ExpressionTarget\"},{\"id\":205,\"name\":\"com.sun.org.apache.xerces.internal.impl.xpath.regex.Token$FixedStringContainer\"},{\"id\":206,\"name\":\"com.sun.org.apache.xerces.internal.impl.xs.SchemaSymbols\"},{\"id\":207,\"name\":\"com.sun.org.apache.xerces.internal.impl.xs.SubstitutionGroupHandler$OneSubGroup\"},{\"id\":208,\"name\":\"com.sun.org.apache.xerces.internal.impl.xs.SubstitutionGroupHandler\"},{\"id\":209,\"name\":\"com.sun.org.apache.xerces.internal.impl.xs.XMLSchemaLoader$LocationArray\"},{\"id\":210,\"name\":\"com.sun.org.apache.xerces.internal.impl.xs.XMLSchemaValidator$LocalIDKey\"},{\"id\":211,\"name\":\"com.sun.org.apache.xerces.internal.impl.xs.XMLSchemaValidator$ShortVector\"},{\"id\":212,\"name\":\"com.sun.org.apache.xerces.internal.impl.xs.XMLSchemaValidator$ValueStoreCache\"},{\"id\":213,\"name\":\"com.sun.org.apache.xerces.internal.impl.xs.XMLSchemaValidator$XPathMatcherStack\"},{\"id\":214,\"name\":\"com.sun.org.apache.xerces.internal.impl.xs.XMLSchemaValidator$XSIErrorReporter\"},{\"id\":215,\"name\":\"com.sun.org.apache.xerces.internal.impl.xs.XSConstraints\"},{\"id\":216,\"name\":\"com.sun.org.apache.xerces.inte